Title : New Shannock Switch, Rhode Island
Text : {{unref|date=June 2014}}
'''New Shannock Switch''' is a small unincorporated village in [[Charlestown, Rhode Island|Charlestown]], [[Rhode Island]], [[United States]]. It is located to the east of the village of [[Shannock Historic District|Shannock]] in [[Richmond, Rhode Island]] and comprises the eastern part of the Shannock Historic District. 

==Overview==
New Shannock Switch is separated from the larger village of Shannock by the [[Pawcatuck River]], which divides the towns of Richmond and Charlestown. [[Amtrak|Amtrak's]] [[Northeast Corridor]] runs through New Shannock Switch after leaving Shannock. After running through the village it crosses the Pawcatuck again, reentering Richmond in the village of [[Kenyon, Rhode Island|Kenyon]].

The Shannock Baptist Church is located in New Shannock Switch, as well as many historic houses. Because it is located in Charlestown, the zip code for the village is 02813.

